RCG Common Denominator Parameter (CDP) Vector
---
The framework is robust precisely because it allows both strict closure (ideal case)
and controlled relaxation (realistic case).

SINGLE UNIFIED CDP
=================

All major datasets constrain overlapping subsets of the same underlying parameter vector.
A highly constrained system with strong cross-predictions and clear falsification criteria.

Data sets:
  • Planck low-ℓ TT          		→ constrains (A_Q, A_D, μ, ν, α, d₀)
  • Planck lensing φ         		→ constrains (k_Q, k_D, A_Q, A_D)
  • Planck EB/TB             		→ constrains (γ_Π, ε_Π, A_Q, axis û)
  • Planck polarization maps 	→ cross-checks A_Q, A_D, γ_Π, ε_Π
  • ACT/SPT lensing          		→ refines (k_Q, k_D, A_Q, A_D)

Common denominator:
  All these observables are different functions of the same
  parameter vector 𝒑, so a single global fit/likelihood over 𝒑
  can be constrained simultaneously by all of them.

